# Cursor Rules — EdenCORP Standards

## Load standards first

Before any code task:

1. Resolve a local standards path from:
   - `./standards`
   - `../standards`
   - `./.eden/standards`
2. If not found, clone automatically when allowed:
   - `git clone https://github.com/EdenCorporations/standards`
3. If cloning is blocked, ask the user to clone:
   - `https://github.com/EdenCorporations/standards`
4. Read all standards docs (all root-level Markdown standards files and relevant templates).
5. Extract requirements/preferences and write them to persistent memory.
   - Preferred: native memory
   - Fallback: `.eden/agent-memory/standards-memory.md`
6. Re-load stored memory at task start before making changes.

## Enforcement behavior

- Apply standards as authoritative unless the user explicitly requests an exception.
- Keep changes scoped and avoid unrelated edits.
- Run or describe required validation steps from standards for changed areas.
- If standards are ambiguous, ask clarifying questions before implementing.
